##
## A propos
##
@node about "About ScriptFTP"

ScriptFTP is a kind of GUI for tools like MountFTP or GetFTP.
It loads an aminet file and allows the user to select files and puts
them in a file (the script). You can add a prefix and a postfix.
eg:
file:    powerful.lha         mods/8voic  68K+Great modules by #?GHy!!
prefix: "Copy "
posfix: "to mydrawer:"

ScriptFTP will add in the script:
Copy mods/8voic/powerful.lha to mydrawer:

You have now a script ready to be use with FTPMount !
With GetFTP you just have to select the files and then execute GetFTP
like this:"FTPGet ftp.luth.se USER anonymous PASS hcll@olivaw.dedal.fr.net
LOCAL MyDrawer: LIST script"
and "script" is the script done by ScriptFTP !

You can search in the aminet file by name, by comment, by directory ....
a file with ScriptFTP.

So ScriptFTP is a selector of files OffLine; You will be able to execute a
script to get the lastest files of aminet while you are chating on the irc
for example

Hope you like it. It is simple but useful (IMHO)

@endnode


