##
## Installation
##
@node install Install

  ScriptFTP uses the mui.library, so you need it ! It is not provided with
the package.

There are two versions of ScriptFTP:
ScriptFTP and ScriptFTP020 (for 68020 or more :-)

You can copy the whole directory ScriptFTP where you like on your HardDisk
(or drag the icon).

Or you can copy the executable in a directory  (or drag the icon), and the
documentation in another one.

ScriptFTP is now localised so copy the files that you need if you are
french.

But the simple way is the installation script !

@endnode


##
## Fonctionnement
##
@node functions "Windows & Menus"

Three things will be explained here: The Main, Search and Option Window


The Main Window:

Well here is the main ListView if you select a file and click on Get it
will be add to the script (easy !)
If you click on Search The Search Window will be actived and ...


The Search Window:

You can make a search by name, directory, comment or on the whole text
of aminet. After selecting one of this mode just type what you want to
search in the gadget string, but -no wildcares- are allowed! (sorry, I
think that this is not very useful)

If ScriptFTP find something it will prints it in the ListView, and you
will be able to get it (add in the script) by pressing the Get button.


The Option Window:

It will be opened at the start if no configuration file is found.


o You have to select the aminet file, the file which will be the script
  file (type a name).

o You can add a prefix and a posfix to the line which will be copied
  in the script if you need it.
  eg:
  file:    powerful.lha         mods/8voic  68K+Great modules by #?GHy!!
  prefix: "Copy "
  posfix: "to mydrawer:"
  ScriptFTP will add in the script:
  Copy mods/8voic/powerful.lha to mydrawer:

  It could be useful with MountFTP for example.

  NB: for the prefix don't forget space! eg: "copy" is different from
      "copy "

o You can select if you want the .readme add in the script
                 if you want the RECENT to be add to the script
                 if you want a EOL after each selection (remove it
                 if you use GetFTP)



o and...
  Now to validate the option click on use (to save option in Env:), or
  save (to save option in Envarc:" or Cancel and it will no take effect
  Clicking on the CloseGadget of the window is the same as Cancel.


Menu:

o Project: View Script     in order to view the script file you did
           About           nothing to explain
           Quit            ... and no more...
           
o Option:  Preference      open the Option Window

@endnode

Important Notes :

The two ListViewers allow you to use multiselection (with shift)
If you double-click on a file it is the same thing as selecting it
and click on the Get button

Important: The script file is not marked, it means that if you
use the same script file as the last time, the news seleted files
will be add to the old script file! Be careful.


I hope you understand my (very ?) bad english and forgive me.

@endnode

##
## NotaBene
##
@node important "Important"

o Important: The script file is not marked, it means that if you
  use the same script file as the last time, the news seleted files
  will be add to the old script file! Be careful.

o The Recent file MUST have this line:
  "|File                Dir        Size Description" 
  but the spaces between File-Dir-Siez-Description can be differents.
  like:
  "|File                   Dir           Size  Description"

  Most of the time the Recent file start like this:

| Recent uploads to ftp.luth.se [130.240.18.2] on 1-Dec-95
| The last 7 days' uploads, newest first. Blank line=new day, + = long .readme
|
|File                Dir        Size Description
|------------------- ---        ---- -----------

so don't worry!

o As ScriptFTP need only the "File...Dir..." line you can use
  ScriptFTP with the Aminet CD too (i use it :-)

o There is an example of a CLI script i use with the script produced by
  ScriptFTP and the tool FTPMount

o Don't forget a space if you need it in the prefix:
  "copy" and "copy " are differents!!

@endnode

